[@Scutellospora nodosa#Misc-exposition*]

[@New observations on the germination shield of the type material of Sc.
nodosa reveal that the shields are hyaline and multiply lobed, which is typical
for Racocetraceae species (e.g. Oehl et al. 2010). Since the species has triplewalled spores (Blaszkowski 1991, Oehl et al. 2008), we transfer it to the genus
Cetraspora Oehl et al. (Racocetraceae).#Misc-exposition*]
